alvarionCdpMIB.name: alvarionCdpMIB

coCdpCacheTable.name: coCdpCacheTable
coCdpCacheTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing the cached information obtained from CDP messages. In tabular form to allow multiple instances on an agent. This table applies to access controllers only.

coCdpCacheEntry.name: coCdpCacheEntry
coCdpCacheEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the coCdpCacheTable. A row contains the information received via CDP on one interface from one device. Entries appear when a CDP advertisement is received from a neighbor device. coCdpCacheDeviceIndex - Uniquely identify a device inside the CDP table.

coCdpCacheDeviceIndex.name: coCdpCacheDeviceIndex
coCdpCacheDeviceIndex.description: A unique value for each device from which CDP messages are received.

coCdpCacheLocalInterface.name: coCdpCacheLocalInterface
coCdpCacheLocalInterface.description: Indicates the name of the interface that received the CDP message.

coCdpCacheAddress.name: coCdpCacheAddress
coCdpCacheAddress.description: Indicates the Ethernet address of the device that sent the CDP message.

coCdpCacheDeviceId.name: coCdpCacheDeviceId
coCdpCacheDeviceId.description: Indicates the Device-ID string as reported in the most recent CDP message. A zero-length string indicates that no Device-ID field (TLV) was reported in the most recent CDP message.

coCdpCacheTimeToLive.name: coCdpCacheTimeToLive
coCdpCacheTimeToLive.description: Indicates the number of seconds to keep the remote device in the cache table after receiving the CDP message.

coCdpCacheCapabilities.name: coCdpCacheCapabilities
coCdpCacheCapabilities.description: Indicates the device's functional capabilities as reported in the most recent CDP message. Possible values are: R - layer 3 router T - a layer 2 transparent bridge B - a layer 2 source-root bridge S - a layer 2 switch (non-spanning tree) r - a layer 3 (non routing) host I - does not forward IGMP Packets to non-routers H - a layer 1 repeater A zero-length string indicates no Capabilities field (TLV) was reported in the most recent CDP message.

coCdpCacheVersion.name: coCdpCacheVersion
coCdpCacheVersion.description: Indicates the Version string as reported in the most recent CDP message. A zero-length string indicates no Version field (TLV) was reported in the most recent CDP message.

coCdpCachePlatform.name: coCdpCachePlatform
coCdpCachePlatform.description: Indicates the Device's Hardware Platform as reported in the most recent CDP message. A zero-length string indicates that no Platform field (TLV) was reported in the most recent CDP message.

coCdpCachePortId.name: coCdpCachePortId
coCdpCachePortId.description: Indicates the Port-ID string as reported in the most recent CDP message. This will typically be the value of the ifName object (e.g., 'Ethernet0'). A zero-length string indicates no Port-ID field (TLV) was reported in the most recent CDP message.

coCdpGlobalMessageInterval.name: coCdpGlobalMessageInterval
coCdpGlobalMessageInterval.description: Specifies the interval at which CDP messages will be generated.

coCdpGlobalHoldTime.name: coCdpGlobalHoldTime
coCdpGlobalHoldTime.description: Specifies the amount of time the receiving device holds CDP messages.

alvarionCdpMIBCompliance.name: alvarionCdpMIBCompliance
alvarionCdpMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the CDP MIB.

alvarionCdpMIBGroup.name: alvarionCdpMIBGroup
alvarionCdpMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects for use with CDP.
